Heavyweights in the Nigerian political scene, business moguls, as well as elder statesmen on Saturday met at the Al-Nur Mosque in Abuja. The gathering was to honour the former Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, Alhaji Nuhu Ribadu, whose son, Ismaila had a ceremony In attendance at the high profile event were the Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo; former Vice President, Atiku Abubakar; former Lagos State Governor and National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Bola Ahmed Tinubu. Others were Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari, Abba Kyari; Katsina State Governor, Aminu Masari; former Sokoto State Governor, Aliyu Wammako; and former Ogun State Governor, Senator Ibikunle Amosun. DAILY POST can report that the environment was cordial as the prominent citizens exchanged pleasantries and banters.